<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1189,2008]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,150,538]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1441,1467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer, 2020" authorityName="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer" authorityYear="2020" box="[326,404,1442,1468]" genus="Hutton" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" rank="genus" status="nov. gen.">Hutton</taxonomicName>
submitted a description of this species to the Transactions and Proceedings of the 
<collectingCountry name="New Zealand" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
Institute issue for 1882, but publication was delayed until 
<date box="[916,1032,1477,1504]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1883-05">May 1883</date>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hutton, F. W." box="[1048,1268,1477,1503]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="134 - 141" refId="ref63079" refString="Hutton, F. W. (1883 d) Descriptions of new land shells. Transactions and Proceedings of the New Zealand Institute, 15, 134 - 141. [May]" type="journal article" year="1883">
<taxonomicName authority="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer, 2020" authorityName="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1048,1128,1477,1503]" genus="Hutton" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" rank="genus" status="nov. gen.">Hutton</taxonomicName>
1883d: 140
</bibRefCitation>
), and was preempted by a brief description in an account of a meeting of the Philosophical Institute of 
<collectingRegion box="[1133,1259,1513,1539]" country="New Zealand" name="Canterbury" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Canterbury</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hutton, F. W." pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="281 - 282" refId="ref62920" refString="Hutton, F. W. (1882 p) Meetings of Societies, Philosophical Institute of Canterbury. Christchurch, 7 th September, 1882. Descriptions of new land shells. The New Zealand Journal of Science, 1 (6), 281 - 282. [November]" type="book chapter" year="1882">
<taxonomicName authority="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer, 2020" authorityName="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1273,1353,1513,1539]" genus="Hutton" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" rank="genus" status="nov. gen.">Hutton</taxonomicName>
1882p: 282
</bibRefCitation>
). A re-description and illustration of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hutton" authorityYear="1882" box="[606,800,1549,1575]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Leptopoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="calva">
<emphasis box="[606,800,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Leptopoma calva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Suter, H." box="[840,1030,1549,1575]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref69528" refString="Suter, H. (1913) Manual of the New Zealand Mollusca. MacKay, Government Printer, Wellington, 1120 pp." type="book" year="1913">Suter (1913: 179</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 35, fig. 1) was based on the type material from 
<collectingRegion box="[309,435,1585,1611]" country="New Zealand" name="Canterbury" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Canterbury</collectingRegion>
Museum. 
<bibRefCitation author="Suter, H." box="[551,745,1585,1611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref69528" refString="Suter, H. (1913) Manual of the New Zealand Mollusca. MacKay, Government Printer, Wellington, 1120 pp." type="book" year="1913">Suter (1913: 179)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Dell, R. K." box="[797,994,1585,1612]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1135 - 1148" refId="ref60044" refString="Dell, R. K. (1955) The land Mollusca of Fiordland, south-west Otago. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 82, 1135 - 1148." type="journal article" year="1955">Dell (1955: 1136)</bibRefCitation>
stated that this species was known from the type specimen only. The latter author noted that 
<bibRefCitation author="Suter, H." box="[726,885,1621,1647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref69528" refString="Suter, H. (1913) Manual of the New Zealand Mollusca. MacKay, Government Printer, Wellington, 1120 pp." type="book" year="1913">Suter’s (1913)</bibRefCitation>
“description and figure are not highly diagnostic. Unfortunately the type cannot at present be located in the 
<collectingRegion box="[783,909,1657,1683]" country="New Zealand" name="Canterbury" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Canterbury</collectingRegion>
Museum, and no topotypes appear to have been collected”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dell, R. K." box="[281,485,1693,1720]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1135 - 1148" refId="ref60044" refString="Dell, R. K. (1955) The land Mollusca of Fiordland, south-west Otago. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 82, 1135 - 1148." type="journal article" year="1955">Dell (1955: 1136)</bibRefCitation>
identified material of “a moderately common shell in Fiordland” as 
<taxonomicName box="[1275,1398,1693,1719]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Murdochia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1275,1398,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Murdochia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[151,232,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">calvum</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer, 2020" authorityName="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer" authorityYear="2020" box="[246,329,1729,1755]" genus="Hutton" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" rank="genus" status="nov. gen.">Hutton</taxonomicName>
), but noted that “until these shells can be critically compared with undoubted specimens of 
<emphasis box="[1348,1429,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">calvum</emphasis>
, the identification cannot be certain”. Marshall &amp; Baker (2007) redescribed 
<taxonomicName authority="Hutton, 1882" authorityName="Hutton" authorityYear="1882" box="[1002,1354,1765,1792]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Leptopoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="calva">
<emphasis box="[1002,1197,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Leptopoma calva</emphasis>
Hutton, 1882
</taxonomicName>
as part of a taxonomic review of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kobelt &amp; Mollendorff, 1897" authorityName="Kobelt &amp; Mollendorff" authorityYear="1897" box="[452,867,1801,1828]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Cytora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[452,530,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Cytora</emphasis>
Kobelt &amp; Möllendorff, 1897
</taxonomicName>
, noting that the shell of this species is distinctive in having a maculate colour pattern, although the latter feature was not mentioned in the descriptions by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hutton, F. W." pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="281 - 282" refId="ref62920" refString="Hutton, F. W. (1882 p) Meetings of Societies, Philosophical Institute of Canterbury. Christchurch, 7 th September, 1882. Descriptions of new land shells. The New Zealand Journal of Science, 1 (6), 281 - 282. [November]" type="book chapter" year="1882">
<taxonomicName authority="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer, 2020" authorityName="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1358,1436,1838,1864]" genus="Hutton" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" rank="genus" status="nov. gen.">Hutton</taxonomicName>
(1882p
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hutton, F. W." box="[247,318,1873,1900]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="134 - 141" refId="ref63079" refString="Hutton, F. W. (1883 d) Descriptions of new land shells. Transactions and Proceedings of the New Zealand Institute, 15, 134 - 141. [May]" type="journal article" year="1883">1883d</bibRefCitation>
) or 
<bibRefCitation author="Suter, H." box="[369,514,1873,1899]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref69528" refString="Suter, H. (1913) Manual of the New Zealand Mollusca. MacKay, Government Printer, Wellington, 1120 pp." type="book" year="1913">Suter (1913)</bibRefCitation>
, and they identified ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[762,885,1873,1899]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Murdochia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[762,885,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Murdochia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[933,1014,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">calvum</emphasis>
’ of 
<bibRefCitation author="Dell, R. K." box="[1064,1196,1873,1900]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1135 - 1148" refId="ref60044" refString="Dell, R. K. (1955) The land Mollusca of Fiordland, south-west Otago. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 82, 1135 - 1148." type="journal article" year="1955">Dell (1955)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall &amp; Barker, 2007" authorityName="Marshall &amp; Barker" authorityYear="2007" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Cytora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mayhillae">
<emphasis box="[1239,1436,1873,1900]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Cytora mayhillae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, B. A. &amp; Barker, G. M." box="[151,437,1909,1935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="49 - 113" refId="ref65739" refString="Marshall, B. A. &amp; Barker, G. M. (2007) A revision of New Zealand landsnails of the genus Cytora Kobelt &amp; Mollendorff, 1897 (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Pupinidae). Tuhinga: Records of the Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa, 18, 49 - 113." type="journal article" year="2007">Marshall &amp; Barker, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, B. A. &amp; Barker, G. M." box="[447,785,1909,1936]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="49 - 113" refId="ref65739" refString="Marshall, B. A. &amp; Barker, G. M. (2007) A revision of New Zealand landsnails of the genus Cytora Kobelt &amp; Mollendorff, 1897 (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Pupinidae). Tuhinga: Records of the Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa, 18, 49 - 113." type="journal article" year="2007">Marshall &amp; Barker (2007: 60)</bibRefCitation>
selected a 
<typeStatus box="[909,998,1910,1936]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority=", NMNZ M." authorityName="NMNZ M." box="[1036,1231,1909,1936]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Leptopoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="calva">
<emphasis box="[1036,1097,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">calva</emphasis>
, NMNZ M.
</taxonomicName>
174790 (pl. 1, fig. C), that “represents the only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobelt &amp; Mollendorff" authorityYear="1897" box="[475,553,1946,1972]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Cytora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,553,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Cytora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species occurring in the vicinity of Greymouth that is accordant with Hutton’s descriptions and 
<bibRefCitation author="Suter, H." box="[340,500,1981,2007]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref69528" refString="Suter, H. (1913) Manual of the New Zealand Mollusca. MacKay, Government Printer, Wellington, 1120 pp." type="book" year="1913">Suter’s (1913)</bibRefCitation>
crude illustration of the 
<typeStatus box="[773,877,1981,2007]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">holotype</typeStatus>
”. This in itself is not sufficient justification for the designation of a 
<typeStatus box="[335,424,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">neotype</typeStatus>
under ICZN Art. 75.3 but, given that previously there had been confusion over the identity of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,243,187,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Leptopoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="calva">
<emphasis box="[182,243,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">calva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we agree that a 
<typeStatus box="[437,526,187,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">neotype</typeStatus>
was required to stabilise the nomenclature. The 
<typeStatus box="[1076,1165,187,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">neotype</typeStatus>
selected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, B. A. &amp; Barker, G. M." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="49 - 113" refId="ref65739" refString="Marshall, B. A. &amp; Barker, G. M. (2007) A revision of New Zealand landsnails of the genus Cytora Kobelt &amp; Mollendorff, 1897 (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Pupinidae). Tuhinga: Records of the Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa, 18, 49 - 113." type="journal article" year="2007">Marshall &amp; Barker (2007: 60)</bibRefCitation>
was from the Otira-Kumara Highway, c. 
<quantity box="[818,889,222,249]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="km" value="45.0">45 km</quantity>
SE of Greymouth; they stated that they had “not seen any reliably localised specimens from Greymouth or the immediate vicinity of that town, so we have chosen the 
<typeStatus box="[195,284,295,321]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">neotype</typeStatus>
from one of the nearest localities where the species is definitely known to occur”. Subsequently, 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Leptopoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="calva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. calva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found living in Omotumotu Bush, Greymouth, and on Peter Ridge, and near Point Elizabeth, on the southern and northern outskirts of the town, respectively (F. Brook pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,150,538]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,431,402,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Current taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Hutton, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Hutton" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[441,769,403,430]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Cytora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="calva">
<emphasis box="[441,591,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cytora calva</emphasis>
(Hutton, 1882)
</taxonomicName>
— 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell, A. W. B." box="[798,1010,402,430]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref67719" refString="Powell, A. W. B. (1957) Shells of New Zealand. 3 rd ed. Whitcombe and Tombs, Christchurch, 202 pp." type="book" year="1957">Powell (1957: 90)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell, A. W. B." box="[1026,1238,402,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref67797" refString="Powell, A. W. B. (1979) New Zealand Mollusca: Marine, Land and Freshwater Shells. Collins, Auckland, xiv + 500 pp." type="book" year="1979">Powell (1979: 85)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, B. A." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="495 - 500" refId="ref65642" refString="Marshall, B. A. (1995) Molluscan and brachiopod taxa introduced by F. W. Hutton in The New Zealand Journal of Science. Journal of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 25 (4), 495 - 500. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.1995.9517499" type="journal article" year="1995">Marshall (1995: 496)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, B. A. &amp; Barker, G. M." box="[217,554,439,466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="49 - 113" refId="ref65739" refString="Marshall, B. A. &amp; Barker, G. M. (2007) A revision of New Zealand landsnails of the genus Cytora Kobelt &amp; Mollendorff, 1897 (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Pupinidae). Tuhinga: Records of the Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa, 18, 49 - 113." type="journal article" year="2007">Marshall &amp; Barker (2007: 60)</bibRefCitation>
, Spencer 
<emphasis box="[664,713,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
., (2009: 203).
</paragraph>
